Where Russia's Attack on Ukraine Was Condemned
‚Ä¢
"While most countries in Europe and the Americas have condemned the¬†Russian invasion of Ukraine,¬†the picture looks a bit more mixed in Asia and Africa."
‚Ä¢
"According to media reports aggregated by Wikipedia, only Japan, South Korea, Taiwan, Singapore, the Philippines, Brunei and Indonesia had spoken out against the attack by Monday night. Many Asian countries ‚Äì among them developing powers India and China ‚Äì have been attempting the tight rope walk of remaining neutral in the current crisis."

Where Europeans Lay Claim to Neighbouring Countries
‚Ä¢
"The Pew Research Center published¬†in depth polling¬†about attitudes towards¬†NATO. As part of that research, they also asked Europeans about their attitudes towards territorial claims in neighbouring countries. When asked "if there are parts of neighbouring countries that really belong to us", 67 percent of Hungarians polled by Pew agreed. Greece and Bulgaria also had high shares of agreement at 60 and 58 percent respectively."
‚Ä¢
"In Russia, where the annexation of Crimea led to an international crisis and global condemnation, 53 percent of those polled agreed that parts of neighbouring countries belong to them. Despite attitudes changing drastically in recent years, three out of ten Germans still feel some of their neighbour's land belongs to their nation while in the United Kingdom the share feeling the same is less but still 23 percent."
‚Ä¢
